(80, 1, 'normal', 'CBSE Kalaosav 2017: Thrissur Sahodaya clinch a hat-trick of titles ', 'Thrissur', 'rszuntitled.png', '', '', 'The three-day event inaugurated on November 23, 2017, witnessed a real festival at the cultural capital of Kerala. From drawing to digital painting, from recitation to drama, from classical music to western concerts and from folk dance to musical instruments, students from length and breadth of the state participated. \r\n', 'Db correspondent', '', '2017-11-27', '<div class=\"gmail_default\"><div class=\"gmail_default\"><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW44012767\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" paraid=\"1275867902\" paraeid=\"{48e5b3a5-21dc-46c7-a0ac-8368dd481cbb}{22}\"><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\">With an extravaganza of artistic expressions, the 26th Kerala State CBSE Youth Festival has concluded on Saturday, as Thrissur </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Sahodaya</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> (1629 points) lifted their title for the overall championship, third in a row. Hosted by </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Chittilappally</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> IES Public School at Thrissur, the three-day art festival saw 8000 participants from 24 </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Sahodaya</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> complexes putting their cultural talents on test in 144 items under four categories on 21 different stages. From drawing to digital painting, from recitation to drama, from classical music to western concerts and from folk dance to musical instruments, students performed to create the real festival at the cultural capital of Kerala.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW44012767\" data-ccp-props=\"{\" 201341983\":0,\"335559739\":160,\"335559740\":259}\"=\"\"> </span></p></div><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW44012767\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" paraid=\"255650271\" paraeid=\"{48e5b3a5-21dc-46c7-a0ac-8368dd481cbb}{26}\"><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\">Malabar </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Sahodaya</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> (1468 points) and Kerala CBSE School </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Sahodaya</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> Ernakulam finished at second and third respectively. With 228 points, Thrissur </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Devamatha</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> CMI Public School came first among the schools in this event inaugurated on November 23, 2017, while Kozhikode </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Devagiri</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> CMI Public School (345 points) won the aggregate trophy. </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Wadakkanchery</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> MLA Anil </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Akkara</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\">, Cine Artist Aparna </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Balamurli</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> and writer Subash Chandran distributed the trophies and honours to winners, while eminent personalities from various fields of art and literature were present during the events and judged the competitions.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW44012767\" data-ccp-props=\"{\" 201341983\":0,\"335559739\":160,\"335559740\":259}\"=\"\"> </span></p></div><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW44012767\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" paraid=\"1134199347\" paraeid=\"{48e5b3a5-21dc-46c7-a0ac-8368dd481cbb}{30}\"><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\">The cultural fest was organised by both Confederation of Kerala </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"SpellingError SCXW44012767\">Sahodaya</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"> Complexes (CKSC) and Kerala CBSE School Managment Association (KSCMA). C Latha Prakash, general convenor and principal, IES Public School, K Unnikrishnan, president, </span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\">CKSC</span></span><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\">, TPM Ibrahim, president, KCSMA, Abraham Thomas, Treasurer, KCSMA, Varkey PT, Treasurer, CKSC, Mukundan, Thrissur president, KCSMA and Francis KA, general secretary, CKSC spoke in the event.</span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW44012767\" data-ccp-props=\"{\" 201341983\":0,\"335559739\":160,\"335559740\":259}\"=\"\"> </span></p></div><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW44012767\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" paraid=\"425254772\" paraeid=\"{48e5b3a5-21dc-46c7-a0ac-8368dd481cbb}{10}\"><span class=\"TextRun SCXW44012767\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW44012767\"></span></span><span class=\"EOP SCXW44012767\" data-ccp-props=\"{\" 201341983\":0,\"335559739\":160,\"335559740\":259}\"=\"\"> </span></p></div></div></div>', '1');
