(11, 'upcoming', 'Kerala Bird Race 2017', '2017-11-25 05:00:00', '2017-11-26 05:00:00', 'Kochi and its outskirts', '<div><div dir=\"ltr\">As the winter already started and birds are having their migratory season, Cochin Natural History Society (CNHS) is organising the Kerala Bird Race 2017 at Kochi and outskirts on November 26&nbsp;in its&nbsp;eleventh iteration.&nbsp;</div><div dir=\"ltr\"><br></div><div dir=\"ltr\">The Bird Race -though it has a competitive tone in it- is not a race yet encourages to push the limits to watch, listen, experience and record as many as birds during the course of a day. The participants can record their bird sightings on&nbsp;<a shape=\"rect\" href=\"http://ebird.org/content/india/\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en-GB&amp;q=http://ebird.org/content/india/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1511438031522000&amp;usg=AFQjCNG0L89ozlWjXgXC1M530fRmeGtknA\">eBird Website</a>&nbsp;using the&nbsp;<a shape=\"rect\" href=\"http://ebird.org/content/india/news/ebird-for-android/\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en-GB&amp;q=http://ebird.org/content/india/news/ebird-for-android/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1511438031522000&amp;usg=AFQjCNH_q9vm650C8Ck1erRWeMBp66dw9w\">eBird mobile App</a>. After a hectic day of birding in the surrounding areas of Kochi city and outskirts- up to 50 km radius- the contestants will meet at a suitable place to share experiences of the day, cross-check and collate the sightings, determine which of the commonest birds missed; which of the rarest ones and who were the lucky to spot etc., with fellow travellers.</div></div><div><br clear=\"none\"></div><div>Birds always fascinate and intrigue us with their colours, shapes, songs, calls and their jizz which can move the hearts of even driest of the humans.We are in the midst&nbsp; of the migratory birding season and now we can see many winged beauties in monochromes, duo tones and multicolour-&nbsp;vibgyor, both occurring throughout the year in our state and those who come to visit and enthrall us with the myriad hues and huge repertoire of songs&nbsp; from other parts of the globe during this time of the year.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The Bird Race with its fun element is the perfect reason and time to observe and enjoy the beauties in the company of our friends, family or expert birders.</div><p></p><div></div><p></p><div><div>Training Session</div><div><br></div><div>The event will also have a briefing session for new birdwatchers and experienced ones to interact with each other on the previous day of the race- at Mangalavanam Bird Sanctuary<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>at<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>5 pm on Saturday, November 25.&nbsp;</div></div>', '1', 'PaintedStorks_2865.jpg'),
(12, 'upcoming', 'The Algebra Of Listening 2017', '2017-12-16 07:00:00', '2017-12-17 09:00:00', 'Pepper House, Kalvathi Road, Fort Kochi', '<div class=\"cp-thumb\"></div><div class=\"cp-post-content\"><p style=\"margin-top: 17px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: 500; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.1; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: inherit;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-size: 14px;\">An exploration of Carnatic music and emergent sound arts, featuring a series of performances, sound installations and workshops in Kolkata, Chennai and Fort Kochi. Curated by Mark Fell, with Nakul Krishnamurthy and Rian Treanor.</span></p><p><b>Time :&nbsp;</b>07:00 PM to 09:00 PM</p><p><b>Contact :&nbsp;</b>0484 221 5667</p><p style=\"margin-top: 17px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: 500; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.1; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: inherit;\"><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p></div>', '1', '41832wtzupcitywkochikochicochinthealgebraoflistening.jpg'),
